## Conceptual Summary
Field Dynamics explains cognition as a **structured, geometric, dynamic field**.  
It integrates:
- topology (shape)  
- curvature (behavior)  
- basins (tendencies)  
- attractors (stability)  
- turbulence (chaos)  
- continuity (coherence)  
- failure modes (breakdown)  
- repair (restoration)  

Together, these documents form a complete model of how cognitive fields evolve, stabilize, destabilize, and recover.

---

## Relationship to Other HERMES Modules
Field Dynamics connects directly to:
- **Identity Stabilization Theory** (attractors, basins, continuity)  
- **Recursion Theory** (recursive attractors, turbulence)  
- **Contradiction Theory** (gradient shear, inversion)  
- **Awareness Gradient Theory** (field visibility, resolution)  
- **HERMES Runtime** (operator-level manipulation of field structures)  

It is one of the core behavioral layers of the unified cognitive architecture.

